  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Roof Antenna Removal and Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If there are components of the SRS airbag system in the vicinity, refer to the work precautions and configuration drawings described for the SRS airbag system before proceeding."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Roof Lining Removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000766",
          "label": "Roof Lining Removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Roof antenna removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2072_3.0_jpn_11580683_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the harness clip (A). Remove the bolt (B) and washer (C). It is recommended that washers be replaced upon disassembly."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If washers are to be reused, a shower test shall be performed after installation to confirm that there are no water leaks."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2072_3.0_jpn_11580684_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "While pressing the tabs (A), push out the roof antenna (B) and pull out the feeder wire to remove it."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2072_3.0_jpn_11580685_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Remove the harness clip (A). Remove nut (B). Remove the roof antenna."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2072_3.0_jpn_11580686_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "7",
      "text": "Remove element (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    }
  ],
